At least 65 British climbers and holidaymakers were feared missing yesterday as the death toll in the Nepal earthquake reached 2,500 .
Up to 18 were killed and more than 60 injured when 7.8-magnitude quake set off a huge avalanche on the world 's highest peak .
Survivors described seeing tents with climbers still inside and tossed into rocks and ice .
At least 65 Britons across the region were unaccounted for .